I"t<p>Sources lists found in:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>/etc/apt/sources.list
/etc/apt/sources.list.d/*
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Apt-get and apt-cache commands go hand-in-hand, whereas aptitude is new and kinda rolls them into one.</p>

<p>There’s a script called:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>dpkg-reconfigure
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>which can walk one through the initial setup of a package that they’d have found when they first installed a package.</p>
